claims:
1. An apparatus 1 having self-organizing neuroplastic behaviors comprising:
A multiplicity of security domains 11
At least one Turing complete calculus 10 for synthesis of said self-organizing neuroplastic behaviors:
At least one bare metal processor 2 configured for executing at leat one said Turing complete calculus 10;
At least one programmable logic 6 operably coupled to the at least one bare metal processor 2 configurable for hosting virtual machine 9 for running software applications 5 and further configured to perform time and again said self-organizing neuroplastic behaviors;
A virtual machine managing means 3 configured for configuring a multiplicity of security domains 11 in said programmable logic 6 operably coupled to both the at least one bare metal processor 2 and the programmable logic 6;
At least one hardware asset 4 configured to provide a first digital data; and
wherein said self-organizing neuroplastic behaviors organize in response to changes in the digital data.
2. The apparatus 1 of claim 1 further comprising software assets 8 for providing a second digital data;
3. The apparatus 1 of claim 1 wherein the at least one bare metal processor 2 is further configured with embedded read-only memory 13 for storing a security algorithm 12 for providing cybersecurity.
4. The apparatus 1 of claim 1 father configured with a memory 7 for storing programs and data.
